narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would highly recommend this course! A wonderfully intimate seminar.

I would absolutely recommend this course to another student. If they are at all interested in the relationship between African/Caribbean authors and the metropole (France), they'll love it. There's a fair amount of reading but it's not so bad if you spread it out over the course of the week.
This is the best french course and in fact best course I have taken at Yale so far. It isn't an easy class in terms of grades but is worth the work.
Absolutely. If you are interested by the topic, there is no reason not to take this great seminar.
if you want to read masterpieces of African and Caribbean literature and get a better understanding of African/ Caribbean
interesting class, though the reading load was excessive at times. Would recommend it if you know you're interested in the material, otherwise it could get quite dry.
